study.name: DOTs Survey AF3
study.introduction: Thanks for agreeing to do the survey! The interview is going to happen in 3 parts. In the first part, I'll ask you about yourself, your thoughts, beliefs, and behaviors. Then I'll ask you some questions about people who are in your life-your social network- and some basic information about them. In the last part, I'll show you a picture that represents your social network and I will ask you to pick 5 people that you want to refer to come into the study. I will explain how to do that in the end. Do you have any questions before we get started?
study.alterPrompt:
This is the last section of the survey. This section is a bit different than what we have done previously. I’m now going to ask you some questions about the people in your life. These might be friends, acquaintances, biological family members, family members by choice, church members, co-workers, lovers, or anyone else in your life. I’m going to ask you to list 20 people you’ve communicated with in the past 30 days. If you have it, I would also like to collect the last four digits of each person’s phone number. This is so we can identify when duplicate people show up in the data. We will not try to contact anyone on your list, though we will ask you to tell five of these people about the study to see if they are willing to participate.

Please list the first name, last initial, and last four cell phone digits of 20 people with whom you have communicated in the past 30 days. This might be communication by phone, email, text, or in person.

It is OK if you use a fake name or nickname to identify these people, as long as you are able to remember it. If you use a fake name, you'll need to tell the person you refer to the study what fake name you used for them.

[Interviewer: Enter first name (space) last initial (space) last 4 digits of cell phone number. e.g., John S 5432]

[Interviewer: Discourage participants from reading from their phones. If they can't think of anymore names, ask "you listed X, is there anyone else like X who you haven't listed yet?"]
study.conclusion: Now, I would like you to take a look at this picture and think about these people, and figure out the 5 people who you are willing to give coupons to refer into our study.
